article.headline: Lehigh 86, Monmouth, N.J. 74
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- CJ McCollum scored 15 points to lead four players in double figures and Lehigh defeated Monmouth (N.J.) 86-74 on Monday night. Rob Keefer and Michael Ojo scored 13 points each and Marquis Hall chipped in 11 for the Mountain Hawks (2-2). Lehigh ended the first half on a 10-4 run, taking a 38-30 lead on a dunk by Gabe Knutson with 2 seconds left in the half. The Mountain Hawks then began the second half with four straight points for a 42-30 lead with 18:09 remaining in the game. Lehigh led by as many as 77-61 on a 3-pointer by Zahir Carrington with 3:23 left. The Mountain Hawks shot 52.6 percent in the game (30 of 57), while turning the ball over just nine times compared to 16 by Monmouth (1-3). Monmouth's Travis Taylor finished with 20 points on 6 of 9 from the field and 8-for-9 from the free-throw line and Will Campbell added 13.
